<br>
I do not believe that the rules of this game were instituted to stifle creativity. On the contrary I think it take a more creative mind to create a unique character within the parameters of the existing rules than it does to wander off into fantastic silliness.<br>
<br>
If someone else wants to play a troll beastlord and attempt to pass him off as an elf that is their business. If they expect me to accept that under the parameters of the game storyline then they are daft. <br>
<br>
It all boils down to one simple point. This game was created with rules. If you wish to create your own there is nothing anyone can do to stop you but do not expect everyone else to indulge you. <br>
<br>
I play White Wolf games as well and believe that I have created some rather unique characters in my time. One is a Glass Walker Ragabash who is a servant of the Weaver. He refuses to shift into any form other than homid believing that it was the Wyld and the chaos that it embodies which drove the Wyrm mad. In his mind the world is doomed without the structure and order that the Weaver provides. He often enters a melancholic depression when he is forced to shift to Crinos due to frenzy.<br>
<br>
My favorite character would be my Malkavian vampire. He set out to learn the arts of Chimerstry in an effort to shatter the illusion of reality and allow others to see the truth in the world. In his madness he began to believe that his own illusions were real. Now it is his goal to kick the collective clutch of sanity out from under the entire race of Cainites. He plans on doing this by mastering the arts of Temporis and traveling back in time to diablerize Caine. It is his belief that all vampires will then spring from his blood and finally embrace the truth of his reality.<br>
<br>
Now whether you think these two characters are original or not are matters of opinion. I do not think that anyone could argue that they exist within the parameters of the rulesets of Werewolf and Vampire though.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately I have known people who played mixed blood vampires (so they could have two sets of disciplines) who had drunk the blood of werewolves (allowing them to possess gifts as well) and had developed powers that would allow them to walk around in the daylight. These people pretty much throw the rules out the window to create their own fantasy world. Is that really creative? I do not think so.<br>
<br>
I guess I can sum this up by saying everyone has a right to play however they want to play. Just keep in mind that some of us play Everquest to PLAY Everquest and not some random fantasy game without rules and regulations. Do not expect everyone to indulge your vices.<br>
<br>
Troll beastlords who are really elves? No.<br>
<br>
Iksar bards? No.<br>
<br>
A human warrior who always wanted to be a paladin but could not because he could never find faith in the true gods yet continues to adhere to a knightly code? Quality. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tuppenfv>Tuppen FV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/5/03 9:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=71>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elven Blade Board BAN</span><hr size=1> Thank you Loganhex.<br>
